<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-08-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-08-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="259" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d259">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 4116/57.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">German
                                Chargé</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-08-24"><hi rend="italic">August 24,
                                1908</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The painful intelligence of the ambassador’s death was received this
                            morning through Dr. Hill and I at once telegraphed directing the
                            President’s condolences to be conveyed to the imperial foreign office. I
                            also cabled directly to the Baroness von Sternberg at Heidelberg.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>